big worry about what

00:04:49.380 --> 00:04:51.410
will happen to the Euro
currency if there is

00:04:51.410 --> 00:04:53.300
a spate of sovereign defaults.

00:04:53.300 --> 00:04:56.514
And in fact, Euro currency
did-- in anticipation

00:04:56.514 --> 00:04:58.305
of the possibility of
default-- it actually

00:04:58.305 --> 00:05:05.170
did depreciate for while
back in 2011 and 2012.

00:05:05.170 --> 00:05:07.710
Now it's pretty much back
where it was before that,

00:05:07.710 --> 00:05:10.430
but it certainly--
there was a fear

00:05:10.430 --> 00:05:14.730
in the market-- which was also
very, very obvious in terms

00:05:14.730 --> 00:05:19.370
of option prices-- that Euro
currency could depreciate

00:05:19.370 --> 00:05:22.950
significantly if, in fact, a
disorderly default did happen.

00:05:22.950 --> 00:05:26.790
Now it didn't happen,
